Therefore, the sign in interval (k, k+1) is (-1)^{sum_{m=k+1}^{10} m}. So, to compute this for each interval (k, k+1), we need to compute sum_{m=k+1}^{10} m. As we saw earlier, sum_{m=k+1}^{10} m = sum_{m=1}^{10} m - sum_{m=1}^k m = 55 - k(k+1)/2. Therefore, the sign is (-1)^{55 - k(k+1)/2}. But we can compute this exponent modulo 2.
